4 ¬∑ Benchmark Protocol

File: benchmark_metrics.py

import numpy as np

def adaptive_band_index(R_series):
    """Compute mean exp(-|R-1|) as scalar health index."""
    return float(np.exp(-np.abs(R_series - 1)).mean())

def bootstrap_confidence(series, func, n=1000):
    vals = [func(np.random.choice(series, len(series), replace=True)) for _ in range(n)]
    return np.percentile(vals, [2.5, 97.5])

def run_benchmark(df):
    A_b = adaptive_band_index(df["R"])
    ci = bootstrap_confidence(df["R"], lambda s: adaptive_band_index(s))
    return {"A_b": A_b, "CI95": ci}

Usage:

res = run_benchmark(df)
print(res)

Output example ‚Üí { "A_b": 0.873, "CI95": [0.842, 0.901] }

‚∏ª

5 ¬∑ Governance Kernel Spec

File: governance_kernel_spec.md

# Tessrax Governance Kernel ‚Äî Adaptive Metabolism Specification (v1.0)

## Purpose
Formally define the minimal equations governing contradiction metabolism and self-regulation.

## Core State Variables
E(t)  : contradiction energy = ¬ΩŒ£ k_i Œ¥_i¬≤  
H(t)  : cross-entropy = information surprise  
·π†(t) : entropy-production rate = lim Œî‚Üí0 Œî/Œît D_KL(p_{t+Œî} || q_t)  
Œ¶_s(t): scar flux = dN_s/dt  
Œ†_s(t): healing power = (1/œÑ)Œ£(-ŒîE_i)  
X_s(t): scar potential = Œî‚Ñ± / ŒîN_s  
R(t)  : regime index = ·π† / (Œ†_s / E‚ÇÄ)  
Œ∫(t)  : coherence susceptibility = Cov_local-fed(Œ∏) / ƒ§¬≤

## Dynamic Relations
1. Free-energy functional  
   ‚Ñ±(t) = E(t) ‚àí ŒªH(t)

2. Onsager flux law  
   Œ¶_s = L_s X_s + Œµ_t

3. Adaptive-band homeorhesis  
   d(cadence)/dt = ‚àíŒ∑ (R‚àí1) + Œæ_t

4. Entropy control  
   Target ·π†* = Œµ‚ÇÅE + Œµ‚ÇÇŒ¶_s

## Calibration
E‚ÇÄ = mean(|ŒîE|) over first œÑ window  
œÑ  = half-life of autocorrelation of R(t)

## Outputs
At each Œît: update {·π†, Œ¶_s, Œ†_s, X_s, R, Œ∫}; log to canonical dataset.

This document is your contract between code and theory‚Äîother modules reference only these variables and equations.

‚∏ª

6 ¬∑ Calibration Routine

File: calibrate_units.py

import numpy as np

def calibrate_units(df, column_E="ŒîE", column_R="R"):
    E0 = np.mean(np.abs(df[column_E]))
    # relaxation half-time via autocorrelation
    Rvals = df[column_R].dropna().values
    n = len(Rvals)//2
    acf = np.corrcoef(Rvals[:-n], Rvals[n:])[0,1]
    œÑ = -np.log(0.5)/np.log(acf) if acf>0 else 1.0
    print(f"E0={E0:.3f}, œÑ={œÑ:.3f}")
    return E0, œÑ

This routine normalizes each run before benchmarking or cross-domain merging.

