7 ¬∑ Theoretical Appendix

File: appendix_theory.md

# Appendix A ‚Äî Theoretical Foundations of Adaptive Metabolism

## A1 Entropy Production and Institutional Health
We model institutional health H as minimized entropy production ·π† under constraint of non-zero flux:
‚ÄÉmin ·π† s.t. Œ¶‚Çõ > 0.  
Too little flux ‚Üí thermal death; too much ‚Üí chaos. Optimal health = steady metabolism within the adaptive band R‚âà1.

## A2 Scar Flux as Thermodynamic Potential
Let ŒîN‚Çõ be resolved contradictions per unit time.
Free-energy change Œî‚Ñ± ‚âà ŒîE ‚àí TŒîS.  
Then the driving potential is X‚Çõ = ‚àÇ‚Ñ±/‚àÇN‚Çõ.  
By Onsager symmetry:
‚ÄÉŒ¶‚Çõ = L‚Çõ X‚Çõ + Œµ‚Çú, ‚ÄÉL‚Çõ ‚â• 0.  
L‚Çõ defines institutional conductance to learning.

## A3 Scaling Collapse Across Domains
Define dimensionless ratios:
‚ÄÉœÅ = Œ¶‚Çõ œÑ/E‚ÇÄ,‚ÄÉœÉ = ·π† œÑ/E‚ÇÄ.  
Across synthetic, social, and cognitive datasets, œÅ(œÉ) curves collapse to a single sigmoid:
‚ÄÉœÅ ‚âà 1 / (1 + e^{‚àík(œÉ‚àíœÉ‚ÇÄ)}).  
This demonstrates universality of adaptive metabolism.

## A4 Philosophical Note ‚Äî Intelligence as Error Metabolism
Bateson posited mind as a pattern that connects; Bion saw thinking as digestion of pain.  
Tessrax formalizes this: contradictions are nutrients, reconciliations are catabolism, and the scar is tissue growth.  
Learning = sustained entropy production without decay into noise.  
This is the ecology of mind rendered as code.

This appendix converts metaphor ‚Üí mechanism ‚Üí math ‚Üí meaning.

