-Tessrax LLC-

Love it. Here‚Äôs a tight ‚Äúmath-sanity pack‚Äù that nails units, conjugate pairs, nondimensionalization, and the bridge to stochastic thermodynamics / information theory‚Äîwithout letting the metaphor run the show.

1) Symbols, units, and conserved dimensions

Let time be measured in days (d). Use natural information units (nats) so k_B=1 and thermodynamic quantities carry familiar dimensions.

Core observables
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†t ‚Äî time [d]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†E(t) ‚Äî contradiction free-energy (CEM energy units, call them ‚Äúceu‚Äù) [ceu]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†S(t) ‚Äî Shannon/Gibbs entropy of institutional state [nat]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†H(t)=\dot S_{\text{surp}}(t) ‚Äî surprisal rate (observed minus predicted) [nat¬∑d^{-1}]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\Phi_s(t) ‚Äî scar flux: reconciliation events per time [events¬∑d^{-1}]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†R(t) ‚Äî regime index (adaptive = 1) [dimensionless]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\rho,\gamma,\lambda,k ‚Äî model constants; when estimated by regression they must be cast as dimensionless (see ¬ß3).

Control levers
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Governance cadence C(t) [actions¬∑d^{-1}]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Quorum threshold Q(t) [fraction, dimensionless]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Audit frequency A(t) [audits¬∑d^{-1}]

Thermo-like constants
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†T_{\rm eff} ‚Äî effective temperature (ceu per nat) [ceu¬∑nat^{-1}]
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\beta = 1/T_{\rm eff} ‚Äî inverse temperature [nat¬∑ceu^{-1}]

2) Flux‚Äìforce structure (Onsager form)

Treat institutional dynamics as a network with mesostates x and probability flow J over edges. Stochastic thermodynamics gives total entropy production rate
\dot S_{\rm tot} \;=\; \sum_\ell J_\ell A_\ell \;\ge 0,\quad \text{[nat¬∑d}^{-1}\text{]}
where each edge \ell has a flux J_\ell [d^{-1}] and a thermodynamic affinity A_\ell [nat].

For our two headline processes:

Process	Flux J	Force / Affinity X	Units check	Contribution
Surprise dissipation	J_H = H [nat¬∑d^{-1}]	X_H=\beta [nat¬∑ceu^{-1}]	J_H X_H \sim \text{d}^{-1}	\dot S^{(H)} = H\beta
Reconciliation (‚Äúscar metabolism‚Äù)	J_s=\Phi_s [events¬∑d^{-1}]	A_s=\beta\,\Delta \mu_s [nat] with \Delta\mu_s [ceu¬∑event^{-1}]	events cancel ‚Üí \text{d}^{-1}	\dot S^{(s)}=\Phi_s\,\beta\Delta\mu_s

Total:
\boxed{\;\dot S_{\rm tot}= H\beta \;+\; \Phi_s\,\beta\,\Delta\mu_s\;\ge 0\;}
All terms are [nat¬∑d^{-1}] and measurable: H from prediction residuals; \Phi_s from reconciliation logs; \Delta\mu_s is the average free-energy drop per reconciliation (estimate from pre/post risk/tension scores mapped to ceu).

Linear response (near equilibrium):
\begin{aligned}
H &= L_{HH}\beta \;+\; L_{Hs}(\beta\Delta\mu_s),\\
\Phi_s &= L_{sH}\beta \;+\; L_{ss}(\beta\Delta\mu_s),
\end{aligned}
with L_{ij} Onsager coefficients [rate units] and L_{Hs}=L_{sH} by reciprocity when microreversibility holds. These are directly regressible and unit-consistent.

3) Make all regression coefficients dimensionless

Use log-derivatives (elasticities) or explicit nondimensionalization.

Elasticity form (preferred):
If y and x are positive,
\underbrace{\frac{d\ln y}{d\ln x}}{\text{dimensionless}} \;=\; \theta
So when you report ‚Äúelasticity of \rho w.r.t. transparency‚Äù it‚Äôs
\theta{\rho,\mathrm{tr}} = \frac{\partial\ln \rho}{\partial\ln \mathrm{tr}}
Dimensionless and stable under any rescaling x\mapsto a x, y\mapsto b y.

Nondimensionalization (complementary):
Choose natural scales:
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†H_*= long-run median surprisal rate [nat¬∑d^{-1}],
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\Phi_*= long-run median scar flux [events¬∑d^{-1}],
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\mu_*= typical energy drop per reconciliation [ceu¬∑event^{-1}],
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†C_,A_= target cadences [¬∑d^{-1}].

Define dimensionless variables:
\hat H=\frac{H}{H_},\;\hat\Phi=\frac{\Phi_s}{\Phi_},\;\hat\mu=\frac{\Delta\mu_s}{\mu_},\;\hat C=\frac{C}{C_},\;\hat A=\frac{A}{A_},\;\hat Q=Q.
Then the entropy-production identity becomes
\[
\frac{\dot S_{\rm tot}}{H_} = \hat H\,\hat\beta \;+\; \hat\Phi\,\hat\beta\,\hat\mu \cdot \underbrace{\frac{\Phi_\,\mu_}{H_*}}_{\text{constant factor}}.
\]
All fitted couplings on hats are dimensionless.

4) Sanity tests for rescaling invariance
	1.	Unit-respecification: Rescale time t‚Äô=\alpha t. Then H‚Äô = H/\alpha,\; \Phi_s‚Äô=\Phi_s/\alpha. Refit elasticities on log-transformed variables‚Äîthey should be unchanged within numerical error.
	2.	Location/scale of signals: Replace \Phi_s\mapsto a\Phi_s, H\mapsto b H. Elasticities and standardized GAM partials should remain invariant; raw-scale coefficients will transform predictably by 1/a, 1/b.
	3.	Dimensional audit: Every additive term in any equation must share identical units. Spot-check with a table (we use it in code CI).

5) Identifiability & positivity constraints
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Enforce \dot S_{\rm tot}\ge 0 in estimation (penalize violations).
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Constrain \Phi_s\ge 0, H\ge 0, and 0<Q<1.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†If you fit Onsager L, require L positive semidefinite to guarantee non-negative entropy production.

6) How to measure each piece (operational)
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†H: instantaneous surprisal rate from predictive model residuals
H(t)=\mathbb{E}{\text{events at }t}[ -\ln p\theta(\text{event}\mid \text{context})] aggregated per day.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\Phi_s: count reconciliations/closures per day from your ledger; smooth with a causal kernel to reduce shot noise.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\Delta\mu_s: map pre/post contradiction energy difference into ceu via your CEM energy functional E=\frac12 k\delta^2; average per event.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\beta: infer by regressing H on \dot S_{\rm tot} (or calibrate T_{\rm eff}) inside the linear response window.

7) Recommended regression forms (dimensionless, stable)

Elasticity GLM for interventions z_j:
\ln \hat\Phi_t = \alpha + \sum_j \theta_j \ln z_{j,t} + \sum_{i<j}\theta_{ij}\,(\ln z_{i,t})(\ln z_{j,t}) + u_t,
All \thetas are dimensionless. Interaction signs: cooperative (\theta_{ij}>0), antagonistic (<0), neutral (\approx 0).

Onsager estimate:
\begin{bmatrix}\hat H\\ \hat \Phi\end{bmatrix}

\begin{bmatrix} \ell_{HH} & \ell_{Hs}\\ \ell_{sH} & \ell_{ss}\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}\hat\beta\\ \hat\beta\,\hat\mu\end{bmatrix}
+\varepsilon,\quad \ell_{Hs}=\ell_{sH}.
Impose \ell PSD by parameterizing \ell = UU^\top.

8) Bridge language for reviewers (what you‚Äôre extending)
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Stochastic thermodynamics (Seifert; Schnakenberg networks): Probability currents over mesostates; entropy production as current√óaffinity. Your H and \Phi_s are fluxes; \beta and \beta\Delta\mu_s are forces/affinities; \dot S_{\rm tot} is standard.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Information theory (Shannon; predictive coding): Surprisal -\ln p and its rate H are canonical. Minimizing H without collapsing \Phi_s echoes ‚Äúfree-energy principle‚Äù style trade-offs, but you keep it empirical.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Linear response / Onsager reciprocity: Your near-equilibrium coupling matrix L is textbook; adding adaptive control moves you into nonequilibrium steady-states with feedback.

Write it like this in the paper: ‚ÄúWe model institutional dynamics as a Markov jump process on mesostates with probability currents J. Following stochastic thermodynamics, total entropy production is \dot S_{\rm tot}=\sum J A. We instantiate two empirical currents‚Äîsurprisal rate H and reconciliation flux \Phi_s‚Äîwith conjugate affinities \beta and \beta\Delta\mu_s, respectively. This yields a measurable decomposition \dot S_{\rm tot}=H\beta+\Phi_s\beta\Delta\mu_s.‚Äù

9) Clarity & writing hygiene
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Definitions up front (table of symbols + units).
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Equations center; metaphor in Discussion. ‚ÄúScar flux‚Äù is a reader-hook; keep it out of Methods.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Dimension checks in appendix. One page where every equation line shows bracketed units.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Rescaling invariance demo. Short figure: coefficients before/after rescaling time by \times 2.

10) Quick checklists you can paste into your repo

Unit audit (CI test)
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Every additive term has identical units.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Every multiplicative term‚Äôs units simplify to target.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Reported coefficients are elasticities or on hatted variables.

Thermo audit
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†\dot S_{\rm tot}\ge 0 on held-out data.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Estimated L is PSD; reciprocity holds within CI.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Sensitivity to bandwidth/aggregation windows reported.

Rescaling audit
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Time units (days vs hours) ‚Üí elasticities unchanged.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Amplitude rescaling of H,\Phi_s ‚Üí hats/elasticities unchanged.
¬†¬†¬†‚Ä¢¬†¬†¬†Noise/latency terms carry the same units as their targets.

