Appendix B ‚Äî Unit Ledger (Physical & Operational Dimensions)

Symbol	Quantity / Meaning	Base Unit (SI-style)	Derived Dimension	Measurement / Estimation Method	Notes / Domain
t	Time	day (d)	T	Timestamp of ledger event	Primary independent variable
E(t)	Contradiction free-energy (CEM energy)	contradiction energy unit (ceu)	ML¬≤T‚Åª¬≤ (eq.)	From CEM model: E=\tfrac12 k \delta^2 where \delta = semantic tension	Proxy for institutional ‚Äústrain‚Äù
S(t)	Shannon/Gibbs entropy of institutional state	nat	‚Äî	S=-\sum p_i \ln p_i over governance states	Info-theoretic entropy
\dot S(t)	Entropy-production rate	nat ¬∑ d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Time derivative of S	System disorder flux
H(t)	Surprisal rate (observed minus predicted)	nat ¬∑ d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Rolling average of -\ln p_\theta(event) per day	Analogous to heat flux
\Phi_s(t)	Scar flux (reconciliations per time)	event ¬∑ d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Ledger count of resolved contradictions / day	‚ÄúMetabolic‚Äù rate of learning
\Delta \mu_s	Free-energy drop per reconciliation	ceu ¬∑ event‚Åª¬π	ML¬≤T‚Åª¬≤ ¬∑ event‚Åª¬π	Mean pre/post tension difference per scar	Conjugate force to \Phi_s
A_s=\beta \Delta \mu_s	Scar affinity (thermodynamic force)	nat	‚Äî	Computed from \beta and \Delta \mu_s	Dimensionless in natural units
T_{\mathrm{eff}}	Effective temperature (energy per nat)	ceu ¬∑ nat‚Åª¬π	ML¬≤T‚Åª¬≤ ¬∑ nat‚Åª¬π	Regression fit from E/S ratio	Governs stochastic fluctuations
\beta=1/T_{\mathrm{eff}}	Inverse temperature	nat ¬∑ ceu‚Åª¬π	‚Äî	Reciprocal of T_{\mathrm{eff}}	Converts energy drops ‚Üí entropy
\dot S_{\text{tot}}	Total entropy production	nat ¬∑ d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	H \beta+ \Phi_s \beta \Delta \mu_s	Must ‚â• 0 for physical validity
R(t)	Regime index (adaptive = 1)	‚Äî	dimensionless	Composite of normalized entropy and flux terms	Defines adaptive band
\varepsilon(t)	Deviation from adaptive band	‚Äî	dimensionless	R ‚àí 1	Control error signal
C(t)	Governance cadence (actions per time)	action ¬∑ d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Event rate from governance kernel	Adjusted by adaptive control
Q(t)	Quorum threshold (fraction of agents)	‚Äî	dimensionless	Proportion needed for consensus	0 < Q < 1 bounded
A(t)	Audit frequency	audit ¬∑ d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Scheduled checks per day	Adaptive governance parameter
\rho	Trust growth rate parameter	d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Fitted logistic rate from trust data	Elasticities dimensionless
\gamma	Belief damping constant	d‚Åª¬π	T‚Åª¬π	Regression on tone / policy consistency	Higher ‚Üí slower adaptation
k	Cognitive rigidity coefficient	ceu ¬∑ bit‚Åª¬π	ML¬≤T‚Åª¬≤ ¬∑ bit‚Åª¬π	From CEM fit: slope of E‚ÄìI curve	Threshold detector for rigidity
I	Information throughput	bit ¬∑ s‚Åª¬π	MT‚Å∞ ?	Derived from message entropy / latency	Input load parameter
I_c	Critical throughput (tipping point)	bit ¬∑ s‚Åª¬π	‚Äî	Value where ‚àÇk/‚àÇI spikes	Defines phase boundary
L_{ij}	Onsager coupling coefficients	d	T	Fit matrix from linear response	Must be PSD for 2nd law
\chi(t)	Coherence ratio (C,Q covariance metric)	‚Äî	dimensionless	\mathrm{Cov}[C,Q]/(\mathrm{Var}[C]+\mathrm{Var}[Q])	0.3‚Äì0.7 = healthy band
\eta_C,\eta_Q	Control learning rates	‚Äî	dimensionless	Tuned coefficients in adaptive update	Small (‚âà 0.01‚Äì0.05)
\xi_{C,Q}	Latency/noise terms	same as C,Q	same	Random draw ‚àº ùí©(0,œÉ¬≤)	Prevent oscillatory lock-in


